Rio Grande Cichlids are pretty cool little critters. This one has the craziest bump I’ve ever seen on one. I caught this one going for Flathead bait. (This one didn’t become bait🥹) this is the biggest I’ve caught so far! Kinda stoked about it. A pretty under appreciated fish. #Fishing #Cichlid #FishKeeping #RioGrande #Bluegill #BluegillFishing #Crappie #CrappieFishing #BassFishing

Every now and then, whilst fishing for the big Redear on Havasu, you run across a hybrid BG/RESF. They max out at around 2.5 lbs and they have their own patterns and spawn time and spawn locations. This one was 1.999 lbs 😂. #Bluegill #Fishing #Fish #Crappie #RedearSunfish #Shellcracker #Havasu #Crappie #Subfish

I GRINDED this spring for a giant largemouth. I ended up catching a ton of 5-8 lbers, and tangled with two real monsters. One threw the hook immediately, but I was able to capitalize on this one. It ate a @6thsensefishing 6” trace swimbait, using a @kastkingusa megajaws reel. New video is UP! Thank you if you watch it!!! #KastKing #Fishing #Swimbait #Largemouth #Bass #BassFishing #SwimbaitFishing #MonsterBass

A Texas paddlefish is apparently a pretty rare critter, so accidentally catching this guy was a real treat! It’s illegal to land them so I guess all you can do is keep the fish in the water and unhook em and watch em swim away, which is good enough for me!
